Titans with Kronos occupied Mt. Othrys, Zeus and the other sons of Kronos entrenched themselves on Mt. Olym- pus. The contest at first was even-matched. In the last resort Zeus brought forward as allies the Cyclops, who fur- nished him thunderbolts‚ and the Hekatoncheires‚ who shook the earth. Sky and earth blazed‚ the earth rocked and was rent asunder, all things seemed about to return to ancient chaos. F inally the sons of Kronos gained the victory. The Titans were hurled down under the earth and there guarded by the Hekatoncheires.

The three sons of Kronos now divided up the government of the universe by lot, As Kronos and Rhea had suc- ceeded Uranos and Gaia, so they themselves gave place to Zeus and Hera, Zeus henceforth being lord of heaven and earth.
